00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,000
"Lost To You."

2
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:58,699
Those who shouldn't get
close, the rain brings together,

3
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,200
and reunites those who
are meant to meet again.

4
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,500
(Episode 3)

5
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:08,083
Class.

6
00:01:08,208 --> 00:01:09,642
First period this afternoon is art class.

7
00:01:09,666 --> 00:01:11,101
Everyone, head to the art room in a bit.

8
00:01:11,125 --> 00:01:12,291
Okay, okay, let's go.

9
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:24,500
I'm terrible at this.

10
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:26,083
It's not so bad.

11
00:01:26,958 --> 00:01:28,375
That problem wasn't too hard.

12
00:01:57,041 --> 00:01:58,333
He came here early by himself.

13
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:00,875
He's setting up the art supplies for us.

14
00:02:02,041 --> 00:02:03,290
He's usually so cold.

15
00:02:03,291 --> 00:02:04,625
I didn't know he was so nice.

16
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:17,708
What are you doing here?

17
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:21,553
Are you the only one allowed to come early?

18
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:26,225
Since you're here, make yourself useful.

19
00:02:27,375 --> 00:02:28,625
You're pretty bossy.

20
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:30,750
Hurry up.

21
00:02:44,625 --> 00:02:46,105
Today, we're doing portrait sketches.

22
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,333
We'll need a model.

23
00:02:47,708 --> 00:02:49,083
Any volunteers?

24
00:02:51,625 --> 00:02:52,625
Teacher.

25
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:55,541
I think...

26
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:57,625
Xu Yuan would be good.

27
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:02,833
Xu Yuan?

28
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:04,625
He can sit still.

29
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:05,916
He's perfect for a model.

30
00:03:08,583 --> 00:03:10,083
Any other volunteers?

31
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:11,166
You go. You go.

32
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:11,833
Mu Zi, Mu Zi.

33
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:12,791
You go. Go on.

34
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:13,916
How about you two go?

35
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:15,118
Why are you telling me to go?

36
00:03:15,458 --> 00:03:15,875
You go. You go.

37
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:17,518
Alright then, Xu Yuan, you can come up.

38
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:28,041
Xu Yuan, relax a little.

39
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:29,875
Look straight ahead.

40
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:31,833
Xu Yuan, your hand.

41
00:03:32,416 --> 00:03:34,000
Can you not be so stiff with your hand?

42
00:03:34,708 --> 00:03:36,083
Dude, relax.

43
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:37,291
Seriously.

44
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:37,958
Can you even do this?

45
00:03:37,958 --> 00:03:38,541
Maybe I should go up there.

46
00:03:38,708 --> 00:03:39,375
Can you turn this way a little?

47
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:40,250
Fine, you go. You go.

48
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,208
How are we supposed to draw this?

49
00:03:41,209 --> 00:03:42,541
I know, he's so stiff.

50
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:43,125
Seriously.

51
00:03:43,208 --> 00:03:44,208
Can he even sit properly?

52
00:03:44,291 --> 00:03:45,291
You go, you go, you go.

53
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:45,875
I already told you to go.

54
00:03:45,876 --> 00:03:47,116
How am I supposed to draw this?

55
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,665
Like this? Who can draw this?

56
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:49,706
He's like a block of wood.

57
00:03:49,791 --> 00:03:51,125
I should've just gone up earlier.

58
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:28,750
Look at this.

59
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:31,375
This is a waste of time.

60
00:06:31,666 --> 00:06:32,666
What bad luck.

61
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:36,625
Jinx.

62
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:38,833
Oh, come on.

63
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:39,958
Such bad luck.

64
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:42,375
Your spatial relationship is off.

65
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:43,583
The perspective is wrong.

66
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:45,041
Teacher.

67
00:06:45,291 --> 00:06:47,041
It's the model's pose that's the problem.

68
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,500
Exactly.

69
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:53,625
Why is today so unlucky?

70
00:06:54,208 --> 00:06:55,333
The jinx is up front.

71
00:06:58,458 --> 00:06:59,458
Teacher.

72
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:01,185
Maybe I should just go back to my seat.

73
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:03,250
No.

74
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:09,125
He Ya.

75
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:11,684
I remember your paint was
leaking last week too, right?

76
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:12,000
I...

77
00:07:12,041 --> 00:07:13,041
And your easel.

78
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:15,309
All the students have
the same drawing boards.

79
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:16,333
How can you blame him?

80
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,184
You blame the model
when you can't draw well.

81
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:20,048
You say it's bad luck
when you drop something.

82
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:21,208
Do you all even know...

83
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:28,791
Do you know...

84
00:07:29,375 --> 00:07:30,916
who organizes your drawing boards...

85
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:32,208
and sets them up for you?

86
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:35,541
Before every art class,

87
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,541
he sets everything up,

88
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:38,188
and you all just take it for granted.

89
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:40,170
But the second there's a
problem, you blame him.

90
00:07:40,666 --> 00:07:41,666
Jinx.

91
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:43,375
Is it really bad luck,

92
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:44,851
or are you just used
to pushing the blame...

93
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:46,791
onto a classmate who won't fight back?

94
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:52,208
You.

95
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:53,583
Sit down.

96
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:00,916
I'm not done drawing yet.

97
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,650
Does this [color] paint well?

98
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,750
Xu Yuan.

99
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:35,166
About earlier...

100
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:36,666
I'm sorry.

101
00:08:41,916 --> 00:08:42,916
That...

102
00:08:43,583 --> 00:08:44,166
The easel.

103
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:46,017
Thanks for warning me about it last week.

104
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:47,121
I didn't take it seriously.

105
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:53,750
I'm sorry.

106
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:01,500
Xu... Xu Yuan.

107
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:03,125
Just now...

108
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:04,684
I shouldn't have said that about you.

109
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:05,708
I'm sorry.

110
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:15,041
Here's your pencil back.

111
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:29,833
Quick, quick.

112
00:09:30,125 --> 00:09:31,205
Find a place to take cover.

113
00:09:36,375 --> 00:09:37,375
Hurry, hurry.

114
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,250
I'll go, I'll go.

115
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:52,142
Zhan Wang, you don't have an umbrella?

116
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:52,625
Come on, come on.

117
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:53,333
Walk with me.

118
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:54,708
Get in here, get in.

119
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:56,916
Run, run!

120
00:09:57,083 --> 00:09:58,283
This rain came out of nowhere.

121
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:07,500
Why don't you come over to my place?

122
00:10:07,583 --> 00:10:08,000
Okay.

123
00:10:08,083 --> 00:10:09,243
I'll show you my gaming gear.

124
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:09,916
I have a ton.

125
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:11,083
Really?

126
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,559
You know what, I'll let
you use my account.

127
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:13,583
Okay, sure.

128
00:10:14,958 --> 00:10:16,059
My account is totally maxed out.

129
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:16,500
I'm telling you,

130
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:17,416
most people don't get to see it.

131
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:18,903
I don't even let them play on it.

132
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:43,601
You had an umbrella and didn't call me.

133
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:46,666
Why do you always walk alone?

134
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,250
This is why.

135
00:10:52,458 --> 00:10:53,658
I don't believe in that stuff.

136
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:56,184
Then let's walk together from now on.

137
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:57,250
Besides, I'm not scared.

138
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,910
And we're going the same way.

139
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:00,666
Okay.

140
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:02,250
Let's go.

141
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,153
About what happened in art class,

142
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:06,208
why weren't you angry?

143
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:08,708
I'm used to it.

144
00:11:08,916 --> 00:11:09,916
They call you a jinx.

145
00:11:10,541 --> 00:11:12,375
They say being near you is bad luck.

146
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:13,375
You don't care about that either?

147
00:11:13,791 --> 00:11:14,791
Let them talk.

148
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:16,286
It doesn't really affect me.

149
00:11:17,291 --> 00:11:18,291
Xu Yuan.

150
00:11:18,916 --> 00:11:20,375
Is there anything you care about?

151
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,000
I care about my family.

152
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:24,625
What about my grandma?

153
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:26,666
Do you care about her?

154
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:27,708
I do.

155
00:11:28,916 --> 00:11:30,516
She was one of the kindest people to me.

156
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:32,125
That's why I hate you.

157
00:11:35,458 --> 00:11:36,458
Why?

158
00:11:36,958 --> 00:11:37,958
Because I don't think...

159
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:41,706
you cared about an old
woman who loved you so much.

160
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:42,875
If you cared,

161
00:11:43,708 --> 00:11:46,308
why didn't you come back to see
her even once in all these years?

162
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:47,750
Zhan Wang.

163
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:49,416
Do you have any regrets?

164
00:11:51,125 --> 00:11:52,125
What?

165
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:53,642
Not seeing your grandma one last time.

166
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:54,666
Do you regret it?

167
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:55,791
None of your business.
[extremely offensively]

168
00:12:03,708 --> 00:12:04,908
I'm not trying to hit a nerve.

169
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:07,708
It's just...

170
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:11,895
The moment you came back to Hong Town,

171
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,813
you went to your grandma's old house.

172
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,833
You remember the height
marks on the wooden frame.

173
00:12:16,916 --> 00:12:18,676
You remember the
osmanthus tree she planted.

174
00:12:19,416 --> 00:12:20,536
You remember her orange cat.

175
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:24,996
That's why I wanted to ask.

176
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:27,750
Since you missed her

177
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:29,250
and thought of her,

178
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:32,226
why did she wait until the very
end without you ever coming back?

179
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:33,250
Enough!

180
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:34,855
You think I didn't want to come back?

181
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:36,083
My dad...

182
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,184
said coming back to Hong Town
meant you were a good-for-nothing.

183
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:40,249
And that I should never get involved...

184
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,250
with anyone from here.

185
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:43,236
Every time I wanted to come back,

186
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:45,416
he was the one who stopped me.

187
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,431
It wasn't until my grandma passed away...

188
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:56,333
that I realized...

189
00:12:58,208 --> 00:13:00,448
I had already lost the most
important person in my life.

190
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:04,583
Only then...

191
00:13:06,375 --> 00:13:07,416
did I start to fight back.

192
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:15,041
So it wasn't that you didn't love your grandma,
it was just that it wasn't your choice.

193
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:33,296
Your grandma gave this
to me before she passed.

194
00:13:34,166 --> 00:13:35,166
She said...

195
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:36,750
that if you ever came back,

196
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:38,791
I should give it to you.

197
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,528
I wasn't going to give it to you.

198
00:13:42,041 --> 00:13:43,601
Because I didn't think you deserved it.

199
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:46,309
Grandma waited for you for so many years.

200
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:47,083
She waited until she was gone.

201
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:48,888
And you only came back to claim the house.

202
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:51,333
I was just so angry.

203
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:54,581
But these past few days...

204
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:57,591
I've realized you're not the
person who I thought you were.

205
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,500
You can read it at home.

206
00:14:01,916 --> 00:14:02,916
I'm leaving now.

207
00:14:19,938 --> 00:14:21,772
(For Wang-wang)

208
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,331
The key to this problem...

209
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:37,735
is the concept of substitution.

210
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:38,911
You take the complex part...

211
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:40,650
and treat it as a single entity.

212
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:41,875
Got it?

213
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:43,166
No.

214
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:48,041
What don't you get?

215
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:49,291
None of it.

216
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:51,101
I'm not cut out for this school stuff.

217
00:14:51,125 --> 00:14:52,125
So just save it.

218
00:14:56,541 --> 00:14:57,541
Paying your debts...

219
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,490
is just how the world works.

220
00:15:00,791 --> 00:15:02,031
Paying it off with your time...

221
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:03,865
was something you agreed to.

222
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:07,990
So what if I'm backing out now?

223
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:09,000
You tell me.

224
00:15:09,041 --> 00:15:10,684
What's the point of these stupid problems?

225
00:15:10,708 --> 00:15:12,468
Will they make my mom
get better any faster?

226
00:15:12,666 --> 00:15:14,726
Or will they stop the debt
collectors from knocking on our door?

227
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:16,166
It gives you the chance of having options.

228
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:18,981
Instead of being like you are now...

229
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,400
constantly on the run from life.

230
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:23,666
Options?

231
00:15:24,166 --> 00:15:25,166
Like you?

232
00:15:25,375 --> 00:15:26,775
Choosing to come back to this dump?

233
00:15:27,583 --> 00:15:28,708
Or like my dad?

234
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:30,483
Choosing to just pack up and leave?

235
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,958
I don't know your family situation.

236
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:35,875
But that's no reason for
you to give up on yourself.

237
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,726
Stop lecturing me when
you don't know a thing.

238
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:40,541
Don't you get it?

239
00:15:40,666 --> 00:15:41,666
I'm not doing this shit.

240
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:42,916
These stupid problems.

241
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:43,833
This stupid town.

242
00:15:44,041 --> 00:15:44,500
And people like you...

243
00:15:44,583 --> 00:15:46,303
with your self-righteous savior complex.

244
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:47,625
It makes me sick.

245
00:16:22,458 --> 00:16:23,458
Wang-wang.

246
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:24,958
My dearest Wang-wang,

247
00:16:26,208 --> 00:16:28,291
By the time you read this letter...

248
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,375
Granny will be gone.

249
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:32,250
Don't be sad.

250
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:34,291
In my life...

251
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:35,791
having you as my grandson...

252
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:37,416
has made me so content.

253
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:39,957
About the house...

254
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,118
don't blame the Xu family.

255
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:42,625
I insisted they take it.

256
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:44,333
Hsu Meixi has had it rough.

257
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:45,958
That boy, Xiao Yuan...

258
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,768
is so much like you were as a child.

259
00:16:48,458 --> 00:16:49,750
But he's quieter than you were.

260
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:51,375
He's much more withdrawn.

261
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:53,625
All that gossip in town...

262
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:54,708
it's like knives.

263
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:55,875
And he endures it all.

264
00:16:57,208 --> 00:16:59,083
Your father's heart is
no longer in Hong Town.

265
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:00,750
But Granny knows...

266
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:02,666
that a part of your heart...

267
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,625
will always remain here by the sea.

268
00:17:05,541 --> 00:17:07,041
Leaving the house to the Xu family...

269
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:08,606
is the same as leaving it to you.

270
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:11,999
You and Xiao Yuan are both lonely children.

271
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,415
You can look out for each other.

272
00:17:13,416 --> 00:17:15,000
That's what makes a family.

273
00:17:15,458 --> 00:17:17,208
The passbook is in the usual spot.

274
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:19,458
The PIN is your birthday.

275
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:20,832
It's not much money.

276
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,208
It's what Granny saved up.

277
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,291
You can use it however you like.

278
00:17:24,958 --> 00:17:25,958
Wang-wang.

279
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:27,791
Remember to eat on time.

280
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:29,416
Bundle up when it's cold.

281
00:17:30,125 --> 00:17:32,000
Don't always be frowning like your father.

282
00:17:32,375 --> 00:17:34,708
Granny will always love you.

283
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:45,041
How shameless.

284
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,374
A whole family, perfectly able-bodied...

285
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:47,434
and they don't go out to earn a living.

286
00:17:47,458 --> 00:17:49,218
Even cheating an old
woman out of her house.

287
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:50,583
By the way.

288
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:51,825
I forgot to mention yesterday.

289
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,041
The house.

290
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:54,291
I'm taking it back.

291
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:55,500
What is it you want?

292
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:56,958
I just want to see...

293
00:17:57,333 --> 00:18:01,146
what kind of person the jinx who conned
my grandma out of her house really is.

294
00:18:01,291 --> 00:18:02,891
Is this how you took care of my grandma?

295
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:04,916
No.

296
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:08,143
Granny Chang never gave me a hard time.

297
00:18:17,708 --> 00:18:18,708
Mom.

298
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:20,601
That shipment at the docks...

299
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:21,976
Uncle Wang didn't try to
lowball you again, did he?

300
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:22,625
No.

301
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:24,184
He was surprisingly reasonable today.

302
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:25,166
It's all thanks to you the other day...

303
00:18:25,208 --> 00:18:26,888
for laying out his accounts so clearly.

304
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:28,458
That's good.

305
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,583
Come on, you two, eat up.

306
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:30,958
I'm full.

307
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,309
I'll go close the courtyard gate.

308
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:33,333
It's raining.

309
00:18:33,875 --> 00:18:34,875
Mom, maybe I should...

310
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:35,916
It's fine, it's fine.

311
00:18:38,041 --> 00:18:38,625
Xiao Wang?

312
00:18:38,791 --> 00:18:39,375
What are you doing here?

313
00:18:39,375 --> 00:18:39,875
Zhan Wang.

314
00:18:39,958 --> 00:18:40,583
Come in, come in.

315
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:41,708
It's raining out there.

316
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:42,958
Why are you getting soaked?

317
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:44,083
Hurry, come inside.

318
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:45,791
Xiao Yuan, go get a dry towel.

319
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:46,956
And find some dry clothes.

320
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,250
Such heavy rain.

321
00:18:51,291 --> 00:18:51,791
Sit, sit.

322
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:53,208
Have a seat.

323
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,000
Have you eaten?

324
00:18:56,541 --> 00:18:57,541
You can eat with us.

325
00:18:57,708 --> 00:18:58,916
I'll get you some hot soup.

326
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:02,083
In this downpour... why didn't you find
somewhere to ride it out? You poor thing.

327
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:03,125
Dry yourself off.

328
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:05,458
Please, don't go to any trouble, Auntie.

329
00:19:05,459 --> 00:19:06,476
It's no trouble, no trouble at all.

330
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:07,500
You just sit.

331
00:19:11,166 --> 00:19:12,166
Zhan Wang.

332
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:15,083
Are you here to see my brother?

333
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,373
The things in the house...

334
00:19:41,666 --> 00:19:42,826
we've barely touched them.

335
00:19:56,166 --> 00:19:57,666
Granny's clivia is still alive, too.

336
00:20:00,291 --> 00:20:02,691
That beat-up old bowl my
grandma used for her money plant...

337
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:05,458
You even kept that?

338
00:20:06,458 --> 00:20:07,738
I couldn't bear to throw it out.

339
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:10,708
Here, here, quickly.

340
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:11,375
Eat up.

341
00:20:11,666 --> 00:20:12,666
It'll warm you up.

342
00:20:12,958 --> 00:20:13,541
Thank you, Auntie.

343
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:14,833
It's nothing. Go on, eat.

344
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:27,916
Your grandma...

345
00:20:27,917 --> 00:20:29,083
she loved eating this so much.

346
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:31,833
When you were little...

347
00:20:32,208 --> 00:20:33,608
back when you were still here...

348
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:34,708
your grandma...

349
00:20:34,709 --> 00:20:36,149
would come to my place to buy it.

350
00:20:36,625 --> 00:20:37,625
She'd say...

351
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:39,150
that Wang-wang is just like her.

352
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:40,750
Even the flavors he likes...

353
00:20:40,916 --> 00:20:41,916
are just like me.

354
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:44,728
When your grandma was still with us...

355
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,523
she was always talking about you.

356
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:48,833
She'd say, "Wang-wang loves to eat this."

357
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,236
"Wang-wang can't stand the cold."

358
00:20:52,416 --> 00:20:53,856
"Wang-wang is the most mischievous."

359
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:57,446
She left a lot of things behind.

360
00:20:58,583 --> 00:20:59,601
I put them all in the house...

361
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:00,985
inside that camphor wood chest.

362
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:02,416
I figured...

363
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:04,125
you'd come back to visit one day.

364
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:25,833
Back when Granny...

365
00:21:25,916 --> 00:21:27,396
insisted on giving us the house...

366
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:30,296
we were going to
write an IOU for its value.

367
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:33,545
And pay Granny Chang
back when we had the money.

368
00:21:35,083 --> 00:21:36,083
But she wouldn't take it.

369
00:21:37,083 --> 00:21:38,843
So we've been taking
care of her ever since.

370
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:43,416
These are all her hospital bills.

371
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:47,166
My mom recorded every single one.

372
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:50,631
Some of the money was
borrowed from neighbors.

373
00:21:51,416 --> 00:21:52,708
We paid it all back slowly.

374
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,500
There's still some left.

375
00:21:58,041 --> 00:22:00,375
To pay off the rest sooner...

376
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:03,958
Mom goes to the docks
for supplies before dawn.

377
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:07,098
At night, after the noodle shop closes...

378
00:22:07,916 --> 00:22:09,333
she takes on piecework.

379
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,541
She has a chronic illness.

380
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:14,708
It's too much for her body to handle.

381
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:15,890
[An unbelievably
depressing promissory note]

382
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:18,166
And my brother...

383
00:22:19,541 --> 00:22:21,392
he has to go to work
every day after school.

384
00:22:21,416 --> 00:22:22,416
Xu Nuo.

385
00:22:32,958 --> 00:22:33,958
I'm sorry.

386
00:22:38,875 --> 00:22:40,250
Can I go see the room?

387
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:36,958
You didn't even move this poster.

388
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:04,250
I saw it before.

389
00:24:05,541 --> 00:24:06,541
And I put it back.

390
00:24:08,625 --> 00:24:10,065
It was waiting for you to return.

391
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:20,750
Auntie.

392
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,541
This money is from my grandma.

393
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:24,500
The PIN is my birthday.

394
00:24:24,708 --> 00:24:25,809
I'll write it down for you in a bit.

395
00:24:25,833 --> 00:24:26,833
Please, take it for now.

396
00:24:27,208 --> 00:24:27,916
Pay off your debts first.

397
00:24:28,125 --> 00:24:28,708
No, we can't.

398
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:30,267
This is the money your
grandma left for you.

399
00:24:30,291 --> 00:24:30,875
We can't take it.

400
00:24:31,125 --> 00:24:32,245
Granny said in her letter...

401
00:24:32,875 --> 00:24:34,666
I can do whatever I
want with this money.

402
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:36,833
I think...

403
00:24:37,166 --> 00:24:38,166
if it's for you two,

404
00:24:39,166 --> 00:24:40,166
Granny would be happy.

405
00:24:41,708 --> 00:24:46,583
It's also to make up for for
all the awful things I said.

406
00:24:48,291 --> 00:24:49,291
Also...

407
00:24:49,875 --> 00:24:50,875
Granny told me

408
00:24:51,541 --> 00:24:52,541
that Xu Yuan and I

409
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:53,990
should look out for each other.

410
00:24:55,625 --> 00:24:56,625
Right?

411
00:24:56,875 --> 00:24:57,875
Friend.

412
00:25:09,250 --> 00:25:09,750
Alright.

413
00:25:10,041 --> 00:25:10,458
Come on.

414
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:11,740
Sit down and eat these noodles.

415
00:25:11,875 --> 00:25:12,955
They're going to get soggy.

416
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:16,208
Xiao Wang, don't leave tonight.

417
00:25:16,708 --> 00:25:17,833
It's still raining outside.

418
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,083
It's dark and not safe.

419
00:25:19,625 --> 00:25:20,625
How about...

420
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:23,541
you share Xiao Yuan's room for the night?

421
00:25:24,208 --> 00:25:25,208
Is that okay?

422
00:25:38,166 --> 00:25:39,166
Does it fit okay?

423
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:44,041
It's fine.

424
00:25:44,166 --> 00:25:45,166
It's just...

425
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:46,870
the clothes are a bit small.

426
00:25:53,291 --> 00:25:54,291
These...

427
00:25:55,166 --> 00:25:56,291
Granny left them for you.

428
00:25:57,541 --> 00:25:58,642
You can look through them first.

429
00:25:58,666 --> 00:25:59,746
I'm going to take a shower.

430
00:26:16,156 --> 00:26:20,832
[A log from October of various expenses
related to Zhan Wang from childhood.]

431
00:26:45,958 --> 00:26:46,958
Granny.

432
00:26:51,833 --> 00:26:52,833
Xu Yuan.

433
00:26:53,583 --> 00:26:54,583
Are you asleep?

434
00:27:00,333 --> 00:27:01,333
Thank you.

435
00:27:04,625 --> 00:27:05,625
You're thanking me?

436
00:27:06,791 --> 00:27:07,791
Thank you...

437
00:27:08,458 --> 00:27:09,778
for taking care of Granny for me.

438
00:27:14,458 --> 00:27:16,018
It was Granny who
took care of me.

439
00:27:17,750 --> 00:27:18,750
Growing up,

440
00:27:20,458 --> 00:27:21,750
besides my mom and Xu Nuo,

441
00:27:22,458 --> 00:27:24,041
everyone else treated me like a jinx.

442
00:27:24,666 --> 00:27:25,666
They stayed clear of me.

443
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:30,916
Only Granny didn't mind.

444
00:27:32,375 --> 00:27:33,815
She always treated me like a friend,

445
00:27:34,333 --> 00:27:35,333
like family.

446
00:27:41,833 --> 00:27:42,833
So...

447
00:27:44,458 --> 00:27:45,818
if Granny treated you like family,

448
00:27:47,291 --> 00:27:48,875
does that mean we're family now too?

449
00:27:51,083 --> 00:27:52,500
Who wants to be family with you?

450
00:27:53,916 --> 00:27:54,916
Fine.

451
00:27:55,208 --> 00:27:56,291
Even if we're not family,

452
00:27:58,166 --> 00:27:59,291
we're friends from now on.

453
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,000
Come on.

454
00:28:04,208 --> 00:28:05,208
Pinky swear.

455
00:28:11,416 --> 00:28:12,416
So childish.

456
00:28:25,458 --> 00:28:27,041
So the jinx actually made a friend.

457
00:28:27,458 --> 00:28:28,458
I know, right?

458
00:28:28,625 --> 00:28:29,291
I heard last night,

459
00:28:29,375 --> 00:28:31,095
he even spent the night at Xu Yuan's place.

460
00:28:34,625 --> 00:28:35,625
Excuse me.

461
00:28:36,541 --> 00:28:37,934
But you weren't that close to Xu Yuan,

462
00:28:37,958 --> 00:28:39,038
and you're just as unlucky.

463
00:28:39,208 --> 00:28:40,688
Can't blame anyone else now, can you?

464
00:28:50,833 --> 00:28:52,713
Their family's dessert
is actually pretty good.

465
00:28:55,750 --> 00:28:57,910
Are you still going to be
my training partner tonight?

466
00:28:59,208 --> 00:29:01,048
You still want me to
be your training partner?

467
00:29:01,208 --> 00:29:02,458
I paid for it.

468
00:29:02,708 --> 00:29:03,948
I want to get my money's worth.

469
00:29:06,583 --> 00:29:07,583
Fine.

470
00:29:07,708 --> 00:29:08,708
But...

471
00:29:10,041 --> 00:29:11,841
you can come to my
place to practice tonight.

472
00:29:13,250 --> 00:29:14,708
It's your granny's old house.

473
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:17,791
You can go back whenever you want.

474
00:29:20,541 --> 00:29:22,375
But let's drop the roleplay.

475
00:29:24,416 --> 00:29:25,458
It sounds weird.

476
00:29:28,041 --> 00:29:28,583
Deal.

477
00:29:29,041 --> 00:29:29,333
Yeah.

478
00:29:29,416 --> 00:29:30,517
I'll bring you a piece next time.

479
00:29:30,541 --> 00:29:31,541
Okay!

480
00:29:35,666 --> 00:29:36,666
Got a pen?

481
00:29:41,250 --> 00:29:42,250
Thanks.

482
00:29:51,041 --> 00:29:52,801
You used the wrong
formula for this problem.

483
00:29:53,375 --> 00:29:55,335
And you're not holding
your pen correctly either.

484
00:29:56,708 --> 00:29:57,708
How should I hold it?

485
00:30:09,708 --> 00:30:10,748
With handwriting this bad,

486
00:30:11,041 --> 00:30:12,521
they'll dock points for presentation.

487
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:18,500
What are you doing?

488
00:30:19,375 --> 00:30:20,375
Do you have any mints?

489
00:30:21,125 --> 00:30:22,125
I want one.

490
00:30:28,666 --> 00:30:29,666
Thanks.

